00:58:46.570 --> 00:58:50.270
that adrenaline epinephrin,
when it's released in the body,

00:58:50.270 --> 00:58:51.910
it doesn't cross the blood brain barrier,

00:58:51.910 --> 00:58:53.510
but there are certain things

00:58:53.510 --> 00:58:56.270
that are able to cross
the blood-brain barrier

00:58:56.270 --> 00:58:57.103
when we are stressed.

00:58:57.103 --> 00:58:59.020
Things like the E2 prostoglandins,

00:58:59.020 --> 00:59:01.140
those cross the blood brain barrier.

00:59:01.140 --> 00:59:03.560
And our blood and our brain,

00:59:03.560 --> 00:59:06.200
therefore our brain and
our body can communicate

00:59:06.200 --> 00:59:09.430
because certain things can
pass through this barrier

00:59:09.430 --> 00:59:11.280
we call the BBB or the
Blood Brain Barrier.

00:59:11.280 --> 00:59:13.440
And also we have something
called the glymphatic system,

00:59:13.440 --> 00:59:14.740
which is really a plumbing system

00:59:14.740 --> 00:59:15.880
that links the brain and body.

00:59:15.880 --> 00:59:19.570
It's the link between the
immune system and the brain.

00:59:19.570 --> 00:59:23.990
Well, there is a set of
actions that we can take

00:59:23.990 --> 00:59:26.450
in order to limit inflammation.

00:59:26.450 --> 00:59:27.640
And this has been shown

00:59:27.640 --> 00:59:30.480
in several quality peer
reviewed studies now

00:59:30.480 --> 00:59:34.650
to reduce inflammation
and to relieve some,

00:59:34.650 --> 00:59:37.750
and in some cases, all of the
symptoms of major depression.

00:59:37.750 --> 00:59:41.680
One of those approaches
is to increase our intake

00:59:41.680 --> 00:59:44.483
of so-called EPAs or
Essential Fatty Acids.

00:59:45.360 --> 00:59:49.240
There's now a very long list of papers

00:59:49.240 --> 00:59:50.760
in quality peer review journals

00:59:50.760 --> 00:59:53.690
showing that when people ingest

00:59:53.690 --> 00:59:58.690
a certain level of EPA
omega-3 fatty acids,

00:59:58.820 --> 01:00:03.820
the relief from depressive
symptoms matches the SSRIs.

01:00:04.520 --> 01:00:05.930
That's incredible, right?

01:00:05.930 --> 01:00:07.410
That essential fatty acids

01:00:07.410 --> 01:00:08.860
could relieve symptoms of depression,

01:00:08.860 --> 01:00:11.820
as well as some of the
prescription antidepressants.

01:00:11.820 --> 01:00:13.910
Now, this doesn't
necessarily mean you run off

01:00:13.910 --> 01:00:15.700
and stop taking your antidepressants

01:00:15.700 --> 01:00:17.420
if you've been prescribed
them, please don't do that.

01:00:17.420 --> 01:00:18.700
Please talk to your physician.

01:00:18.700 --> 01:00:22.530
And I should mention that
some of the same studies

01:00:22.530 --> 01:00:24.600
have shown that increasing our intake

01:00:24.600 --> 01:00:26.010
of these essential fatty acids,

01:00:26.010 --> 01:00:30.870
in particular, the EPA
variety of omega-3s,

01:00:30.870 --> 01:00:35.720
can lower the effective
dose of things like SSRIs.

01:00:35.720 --> 01:00:39.300
Meaning if we required a 50
milligram or 40 milligram dose

01:00:39.300 --> 01:00:42.870
of fluoxetine, that one
can get by on a lower dose

01:00:42.870 --> 01:00:46.390
and thereby perhaps not experience as many

01:00:46.390 --> 01:00:47.930
or as severe side effects

01:00:47.930 --> 01:00:50.293
by taking or supplementing with EPAs.

01:00:51.270 --> 01:00:55.010
Now, the threshold level
seems to be about one gram,

01:00:55.010 --> 01:00:57.180
1000 milligrams of EPA.

01:00:57.180 --> 01:01:00.360
So you will sometimes see
on a bottle of krill oil

01:01:00.360 --> 01:01:04.010
or fish oil or any other
source, even plant source

01:01:04.010 --> 01:01:08.870
or other source of EPA
that it's 1000 milligrams

01:01:08.870 --> 01:01:10.400
or 1200 milligrams.

01:01:10.400 --> 01:01:12.170
But what's really important to look at

01:01:12.170 --> 01:01:16.830
is whether or not there's more
than 1000 milligrams of EPA,

01:01:16.830 --> 01:01:19.340
because the EPA in particular
is what's important here.

01:01:19.340 --> 01:01:22.310
And actually in exploring
some of the literature

01:01:22.310 --> 01:01:26.150
on the effects of EPAs on
cardiovascular health, excuse me,

01:01:26.150 --> 01:01:28.740
as well as their effects on depression,

01:01:28.740 --> 01:01:32.020
there's some interesting
dose dependent responses,

01:01:32.020 --> 01:01:36.040
such that people who took
anywhere from 400 milligrams

01:01:36.040 --> 01:01:39.270
to 5,000 milligrams of EPAs,

01:01:39.270 --> 01:01:41.560
achieved a variety of different benefits.

01:01:41.560 --> 01:01:43.300
And in some cases, some side effects,

01:01:43.300 --> 01:01:44.450
we'll talk about those.

01:01:45.350 --> 01:01:47.330
And it does seem that this 1000 milligrams

01:01:47.330 --> 01:01:50.490
is the critical threshold for benefiting

01:01:50.490 --> 01:01:52.760
or getting some relief
from depressive symptoms.

01:01:52.760 --> 01:01:55.400
But people who took two
grams seem to do better.

01:01:55.400 --> 01:01:57.720
And in the cardiovascular health realm,

01:01:57.720 --> 01:01:59.720
there it's a little more complicated.

01:01:59.720 --> 01:02:03.100
Some studies point to
a very positive effect

01:02:03.100 --> 01:02:04.240
on cardiovascular health

01:02:04.240 --> 01:02:08.193
by taking increasing amounts
of EPA, others, not so much.

01:02:09.170 --> 01:02:11.300
The current data point to the fact

01:02:11.300 --> 01:02:13.920
that for every gram of
EPA that one ingest,

01:02:13.920 --> 01:02:17.250
there's about a 9% improvement
in cardiovascular health,

01:02:17.250 --> 01:02:21.776
the same dose dependent
improvement on psychological health

01:02:21.776 --> 01:02:25.630
in combating depression
can't really be stated.

01:02:25.630 --> 01:02:28.250
I wouldn't say that the more EPA you take,

01:02:28.250 --> 01:02:30.260
the better you're going
to feel so to speak.

01:02:30.260 --> 01:02:32.780
I don't think the data point to that.

01:02:32.780 --> 01:02:35.580
However, it does seem
that if you take a gram,

01:02:35.580 --> 01:02:38.470
1000 milligrams or 2000 milligrams of EPA,

01:02:38.470 --> 01:02:40.870
there does seem to be
some substantial relief

01:02:40.870 --> 01:02:43.540
for many people, should
emphasize many, not all,

01:02:43.540 --> 01:02:47.840
for many people in major
depressive symptoms.

01:02:47.840 --> 01:02:49.280
So how would this work?

01:02:49.280 --> 01:02:52.063
Well, turns out that these
inflammatory cytokines,

01:02:53.120 --> 01:02:56.640
they impact neurons and
the circuits of the brain

01:02:56.640 --> 01:02:58.390
that relate to things like serotonin,

01:02:58.390 --> 01:03:00.600
dopamine, and norepinephrine.

01:03:00.600 --> 01:03:02.430
These inflammatory cytokines

01:03:02.430 --> 01:03:04.410
act in a variety of different ways,

01:03:04.410 --> 01:03:07.350
but they mainly act to inhibit
the release of serotonin,

01:03:07.350 --> 01:03:12.040
norepinephrine, and dopamine,
or the synthesis of serotonin,

01:03:12.040 --> 01:03:13.380
norepinephrine and dopamine.

01:03:13.380 --> 01:03:16.180
And I'll give you one example of how EPAs

01:03:16.180 --> 01:03:18.100
can positively impact this process.

01:03:18.100 --> 01:03:19.900
And then it points to a second tool,

01:03:19.900 --> 01:03:22.780
which is the proper
utilization of exercise

01:03:22.780 --> 01:03:26.950
to offset the effects of depression.

01:03:26.950 --> 01:03:29.450
So now you should understand
why having healthy levels

01:03:29.450 --> 01:03:32.820
of serotonin is important
for maintaining healthy mood.

01:03:32.820 --> 01:03:35.890
It's not responsible for all the aspects

01:03:35.890 --> 01:03:37.183
of having a healthy mood,

01:03:38.020 --> 01:03:39.610
there's also dopamine and norepinephrine,

01:03:39.610 --> 01:03:41.840
but it is a very important one.

01:03:41.840 --> 01:03:44.033
Dopamine also called 5HT,

01:03:46.320 --> 01:03:50.600
essentially derives from a
precursor called tryptophan.

01:03:50.600 --> 01:03:54.470
Tryptophan arrives into our
system through our diet,

01:03:54.470 --> 01:03:56.840
okay, tryptophan is an amino acid.

01:03:56.840 --> 01:04:01.670
Tryptophan is found in Turkey,
it's found in carbohydrates.

01:04:01.670 --> 01:04:04.070
And that should therefore raise the idea,

01:04:04.070 --> 01:04:06.120
hmm, I wonder if one of
the reasons why people

01:04:06.120 --> 01:04:07.770
who are depressed have such an appetite

01:04:07.770 --> 01:04:09.400
for carbohydrate late in foods

01:04:09.400 --> 01:04:12.250
is because they're trying
to get more tryptophan,

01:04:12.250 --> 01:04:14.000
and therefore more serotonin.

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:15.563
And indeed that's the case.

01:04:16.770 --> 01:04:19.860
Tryptophan is eventually
converted into serotonin.

01:04:19.860 --> 01:04:23.423
However, if there's excessive
amounts of inflammation,

01:04:24.560 --> 01:04:28.747
these inflammatory
cytokines cause tryptophan

01:04:28.747 --> 01:04:31.670
to not be converted so
much into serotonin,

01:04:31.670 --> 01:04:34.223
but to be diverted down
a different pathway.

01:04:35.500 --> 01:04:38.790
The pathway involves something
called IDO, Indoleamine,

01:04:38.790 --> 01:04:41.803
which converts tryptophan into kynurenine.

01:04:43.545 --> 01:04:46.040
Kynurenine actually acts as a neurotoxin

01:04:47.070 --> 01:04:50.713
by way of converting into
something called quinolinic acid.

01:04:51.590 --> 01:04:53.540
And quinolinic acid is pro depressive.

01:04:53.540 --> 01:04:55.960
So if that seems like a
complicated biochemical pathway,

01:04:55.960 --> 01:04:58.260
what's basically happening
here is that the tryptophan

01:04:58.260 --> 01:05:00.563
that normally would be
made into serotonin,

01:05:01.470 --> 01:05:03.740
under conditions of
inflammation is being diverted

01:05:03.740 --> 01:05:06.290
into a neurotoxic pathway.

01:05:06.290 --> 01:05:08.070
And ingestion of EPAs,

01:05:08.070 --> 01:05:11.180
because it limits these
inflammatory cytokines,

01:05:11.180 --> 01:05:13.883
things like IL-6, C-reactive
protein, et cetera,

01:05:15.500 --> 01:05:19.940
can cause more of the
tryptophan that one ingests

01:05:19.940 --> 01:05:21.960
or has in their body to be diverted

01:05:21.960 --> 01:05:23.833
towards the serotoninergic pathway.

01:05:25.670 --> 01:05:30.030
Exercise, it turns out,
also has a positive effect

01:05:30.030 --> 01:05:34.080
on the tryptophan to
serotonin conversion pathway.

01:05:34.080 --> 01:05:35.930
And the way it does it
is really interesting.

01:05:35.930 --> 01:05:38.570
You now know that tryptophan
can either be converted

01:05:38.570 --> 01:05:41.330
into serotonin or it can be
converted into this neurotoxin,

01:05:41.330 --> 01:05:42.483
which is a bad thing.

01:05:43.860 --> 01:05:46.310
Exercise, the activation of the muscles

01:05:46.310 --> 01:05:47.920
through rhythmic repeated use,

01:05:47.920 --> 01:05:51.060
in particular aerobic exercise,
but also resistance training

01:05:51.060 --> 01:05:53.500
has been shown to do this to some extent,

01:05:53.500 --> 01:05:58.360
tends to sequester or shuttle
the contouring into the muscle

01:05:58.360 --> 01:06:01.350
so that it isn't converted
into this neurotoxin

01:06:01.350 --> 01:06:03.930
that is pro depression, okay?

01:06:03.930 --> 01:06:05.160
There are a lot of steps in the pathway

01:06:05.160 --> 01:06:06.670
leading to depression,

01:06:06.670 --> 01:06:08.150
but what this essentially means

01:06:08.150 --> 01:06:12.410
is that hitting a certain
threshold level of EPA intake,

01:06:12.410 --> 01:06:15.530
whether by supplementation
with fish oil or krill oil

01:06:15.530 --> 01:06:16.940
or through some plant source

01:06:16.940 --> 01:06:19.760
if you're not into
ingesting fish or krill,

01:06:19.760 --> 01:06:23.890
or trying to get up above
that 1000 milligram threshold

01:06:23.890 --> 01:06:25.970
for EPA by ingesting
particular food sources,

01:06:25.970 --> 01:06:27.080
you certainly can do it through food,

01:06:27.080 --> 01:06:28.580
you don't have to supplement,

01:06:28.580 --> 01:06:30.530
but it's easier to do with supplements,

01:06:31.410 --> 01:06:33.660
that doing that will
limit the inflammation

01:06:33.660 --> 01:06:36.800
that diverts tryptophan into
this neurotoxic pathway.

01:06:36.800 --> 01:06:41.800
And exercise as well, augments
this conversion of tryptophan

01:06:42.530 --> 01:06:45.930
into serotonin because it takes this thing

01:06:45.930 --> 01:06:49.920
that would potentially be a
neurotoxin and it sequesters it,

01:06:49.920 --> 01:06:52.260
it pulls it away so that it can't actually

01:06:52.260 --> 01:06:54.570
go have its pro depressive effects.

01:06:54.570 --> 01:06:57.040
So you've got multiple steps here.

01:06:57.040 --> 01:06:59.230
We're describing two tools,

01:06:59.230 --> 01:07:01.560
increasing EPA and regular exercise

01:07:01.560 --> 01:07:04.000
as a way of increasing serotonin,

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:05.630
somewhat indirectly, right?

01:07:05.630 --> 01:07:07.510
It's by limiting this bad pathway

01:07:07.510 --> 01:07:10.250
to promote the activity of a good pathway.

01:07:10.250 --> 01:07:12.530
But from the data that are published

01:07:12.530 --> 01:07:13.860
in Quality Peer Review journals,

01:07:13.860 --> 01:07:15.760
it really appears that
this inflammation pathway

01:07:15.760 --> 01:07:19.280
does function to increase
depression through these pathways.

01:07:19.280 --> 01:07:21.410
And so knowing that there
are behavioral steps

01:07:21.410 --> 01:07:23.010
and supplementation based steps,

01:07:23.010 --> 01:07:26.990
or if you prefer getting
your EPAs from typical food,

01:07:26.990 --> 01:07:29.620
from nutritional approaches,

01:07:29.620 --> 01:07:32.620
I find that very reassuring
that the mechanisms

01:07:32.620 --> 01:07:35.400
all converge on a common
pathway, serotonin.

01:07:35.400 --> 01:07:38.930
That gives me great peace of
mind that when people say,

01:07:38.930 --> 01:07:40.880
hey, go out for a run,

01:07:40.880 --> 01:07:42.630
or you should get outdoors exercise,

01:07:42.630 --> 01:07:45.570
or you should take fish oil
like the Scandinavians do,

01:07:45.570 --> 01:07:49.880
I have Scandinavian family
members and they are known to,

01:07:49.880 --> 01:07:52.320
or I should say they are
quite open about the fact

01:07:52.320 --> 01:07:54.110
that during the winter
months in particular

01:07:54.110 --> 01:07:55.960
when depression is more likely,

01:07:55.960 --> 01:07:57.450
but throughout the year, really,

01:07:57.450 --> 01:08:01.980
they make an effort to regularly
ingest high levels of EPA,

01:08:01.980 --> 01:08:06.220
either through ingesting
fatty fish and its skin,

01:08:06.220 --> 01:08:07.690
I'm not a particular fan of ingesting

01:08:07.690 --> 01:08:08.580
the skin of fatty fish,

01:08:08.580 --> 01:08:10.790
or by supplementing with Cod liver oil

01:08:10.790 --> 01:08:12.500
or other types of fish oil, sardines,

01:08:12.500 --> 01:08:14.590
and things of that sort, sardine oils.

01:08:14.590 --> 01:08:15.840
There are a number of
different things out there

01:08:15.840 --> 01:08:17.270
that one could use.

01:08:17.270 --> 01:08:19.610
So I find it very reassuring

01:08:19.610 --> 01:08:21.710
that there's a common biochemical pathway

01:08:21.710 --> 01:08:24.860
that can explain why these
things not just work,

01:08:24.860 --> 01:08:26.550
but why they should work.

01:08:26.550 --> 01:08:28.090
They should work because they operate

01:08:28.090 --> 01:08:30.570
in the very same biochemical pathways

01:08:30.570 --> 01:08:34.730
that antidepressants that
are prescribed to people do.

01:08:34.730 --> 01:08:35.800
So what does this mean for you?

01:08:35.800 --> 01:08:38.740
Well, if you're somebody who
suffers from major depression,

01:08:38.740 --> 01:08:41.080
again, don't stop taking
your prescribed medication.

01:08:41.080 --> 01:08:41.913
Talk to your doctor,

01:08:41.913 --> 01:08:46.913
but talk to them perhaps
about the EPAs and exercise

01:08:47.020 --> 01:08:48.410
and how these things can impinge

01:08:48.410 --> 01:08:50.190
on the same biochemical pathways.

01:08:50.190 --> 01:08:51.420
If you're somebody who is not suffering

01:08:51.420 --> 01:08:53.710
from major depression, I
still think these pathways

01:08:53.710 --> 01:08:55.550
are really important to understand.

01:08:55.550 --> 01:08:59.900
And actually knowing these
pathways is additional motivation

01:08:59.900 --> 01:09:01.150
